---
title: Crispy Buffalo Tofu Sandwiches with Blue Cheese Dressing, Potato Wedges & Mixed Greens Salad
description: Bright, bold Buffalo sauce and blue cheese dressing elevate this crispy tofu sandwich to delicious new heights. You'll fry up battered tofu and load onto a pillowy buns along with crisp quick-pickled cucumbers. Roasted seasoned potato wedges, plus a mixed green salad with ranch dressing, round out the plate.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/67bc2f51fb63c027ee47259a-50e7defa.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/67bc2f51fb63c027ee47259a-en-US.pdf
time required: 35 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/crispy-buffalo-tofu-sandwiches-67bc2f51fb63c027ee47259a
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 1320 kcal
  fat: 64 g
  saturated fat: 16 g
  carbohydrates: 145 g
  sugar: 19 g
  protein: 35 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 3020 mg
servings: 2
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

In a shallow #dish{}, whisk @tempura batter{82%g} with 1/2 cup cold water. Place
@panko breadcrumbs{1%cup} in a separate shallow dish.

Cut @potatoes{12%oz} into 1/2-inch-thick wedges. Trim and thinly slice
@mini cucumber{1} into rounds. Halve @tofu{1} crosswise, then slice each half
widthwise (you'll have four thin, square planks). Season tofu with half the
@Frank's seasoning blend{1/4%oz}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{},
@fry seasoning{1%tbsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned
and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

In a #small bowl{}, toss cucumber with 1/2 tsp @sugar{1/2%tsp} and 1/4 tsp
@salt{1/4%tsp}. Set aside to marinate, tossing occasionally.

Add tofu to dish with tempura batter; turn to coat.

> TIP: Use a fork to gently turn tofu in batter and transfer to next dish.

Transfer tofu to dish with panko and turn to coat, pressing to adhere.

Heat a 1/3-inch layer of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat.
Once oil is hot enough that a pinch of panko sizzles when added to the pan, add
coated tofu. Cook until golden brown, ~{2-4%minutes} per side (if tofu begins to
brown too quickly, lower the heat!). Transfer to a paper-towel-lined
#plate{}.

While tofu cooks, in a second small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine
@Frank's hot sauce{3%units}, 2 TBSP @butter{2%tbsp}, 1 tsp @water{1%tsp}, and
1/4 tsp @salt{1/4%tsp}. Cover with #plastic wrap{} and microwave until butter
has mostly melted, ~{20-25%seconds}. Stir until mixture is smooth. Add
remaining @Frank's seasoning blend{1/4%oz} and stir until thoroughly combined.

Drizzle tofu with as much Buffalo sauce as you like.

Halve and toast @brioche buns{2}(halved) in a #toaster{}.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, toss @mixed greens{2%oz} with as much
@buttermilk ranch dressing{1.5%oz} as you like. Taste and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

Transfer cucumber to a paper-towel-lined plate. Cover with a second paper towel
and press firmly to absorb any excess liquid.

Spread top buns with as much @blue cheese dressing{1.5%oz} as you like. Fill
bottom buns with Buffalo tofu and cucumber. Close to form sandwiches.

Divide sandwiches, potato wedges, and salad between plates. Serve with any
remaining ranch dressing and any remaining blue cheese dressing on the side.